TY  - JOUR
AB  - Implicit markets capture compensation for intraurban and interregional differences in amenities and yield differences in housing prices and wages. These pecuniary differences become preference-based weights in a quality of life index. Hedonic equations are estimated using micro data from the 1980 Census and assembled county-based amenity data on climatic, environmental, and urban conditions. Ranking of 253 urban counties reveals substantial variation within and among urban areas.
